### THEORY - Self in python  - It allows methods within that class to access and modify the attributes and other methods belonging to that unique object. 

When you create an object (instance) from a class, self represents that specific object
in memory. This ensures that if you have multiple objects of the same class (e.g., car1 and car2),
each can have its own unique data.
Mandatory First Parameter: Every instance method must include self as its first parameter 
in its definition. For example, def my_method(self):.
